{"title_page": "Udhowali Khurd", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Udhowali Khurd\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| settlement_type         = Village\n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates             = \n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Gurdaspur district|Gurdaspur]]\n| subdivision_type3       = Tehsil\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Dera Baba Nanak]]\n| subdivision_type4       = Region\n| subdivision_name4       = [[Majha]]\n| government_type         = [[Panchayati raj (India)|Panchayat raj]]\n| governing_body          = [[Gram panchayat]]\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n<!-- ALL fields with measurements have automatic unit conversion -->\n<!-- for references: use <ref>tags -->\n| elevation_m             = \n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_blank2_title = Total Households\n| population_blank2      = 266\n| population_footnotes    =\n| population_total        = 1411<br/><small>751/660 [[male|\u2642]]/[[female|\u2640]]</small>\n| population_density_km2  = \n| population_note         = \n| population_blank1_title = Scheduled Castes\n| population_blank1      = 63<br/><small>32/31 [[male|\u2642]]/[[female|\u2640]]</small>\n| population_demonym      = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]\n| demographics1_title2    = \n| demographics1_info2     = \n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_total_ha           = 231\n| area_code_type          = Telephone\n| area_code               = 01871<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-04-18|title=Telephone directory of Gurdaspur district|url=http://gurdaspur.nic.in/html/telephone_directory.htm|website=gurdaspur.nic.in}}</ref>\n| registration_plate      =\n| iso_code                = IN-PB\n| blank1_name_sec2        = \n| blank1_info_sec2        = \n| website                 = {{URL|gurdaspur.nic.in}}\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Udhowali Khurd''' is a village in [[Dera Baba Nanak]] in [[Gurdaspur district]] of [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] [[States and territories of India|State]], India. It is located {{convert|19|km}} from sub district headquarter and {{convert|40|km}} from district headquarter. The village is [[Administration (government)|administrated]] by [[Sarpanch]] an elected representative of the village.\n\n== Demography ==\n{{as of|2011}}, The village has a total number of 266 houses and the population of 1411 of which 751 are males while 660 are females.<ref name=census>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/DCHB_Village_Release_0300.xlsx|title=DCHB Village Release|work=[[Census of India, 2011]]}}</ref>  According to the report [[published]] by [[Census India]] in 2011, out of the total population of the village 63 people are from [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Schedule Caste]] and the village does not have any [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Schedule Tribe]] population so far.<ref name=census /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=103437|title=Child Sex Ratio in India (2001-2011)|work=pib.nic.in}}</ref><ref name=census />\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of villages in India]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.punjabtourism.gov.in/ Tourism of Punjab]\n* [http://punjabcensus.gov.in/ Census of Punjab]\n\n{{Gurdaspur district}}\n\n{{coord|31|57|N|75|02|E|display=title|region:IN_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Gurdaspur district]]\n\n\n{{Gurdaspur-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Udhowali Khurd\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| settlement_type         = Village\n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates             = \n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Gurdaspur district|Gurdaspur]]\n| subdivision_type3       = Tehsil\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Dera Baba Nanak]]\n| subdivision_type4       = Region\n| subdivision_name4       = [[Majha]]\n| government_type         = [[Panchayati raj (India)|Panchayat raj]]\n| governing_body          = [[Gram panchayat]]\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n<!-- ALL fields with measurements have automatic unit conversion -->\n<!-- for references: use <ref>tags -->\n| elevation_m             = \n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_blank2_title = Total Households\n| population_blank2      = 266\n| population_footnotes    =\n| population_total        = 1411<br/><small>751/660 [[male|\u2642]]/[[female|\u2640]]</small>\n| population_density_km2  = \n| population_note         = \n| population_blank1_title = Scheduled Castes\n| population_blank1      = 63<br/><small>32/31 [[male|\u2642]]/[[female|\u2640]]</small>\n| population_demonym      = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]\n| demographics1_title2    = \n| demographics1_info2     = \n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_total_ha           = 231\n| area_code_type          = Telephone\n| area_code               = 01871<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-04-18|title=Telephone directory of Gurdaspur district|url=http://gurdaspur.nic.in/html/telephone_directory.htm|website=gurdaspur.nic.in}}</ref>\n| registration_plate      =\n| iso_code                = IN-PB\n| blank1_name_sec2        = \n| blank1_info_sec2        = \n| website                 = {{URL|gurdaspur.nic.in}}\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Udhowali Khurd''' is a village in [[Dera Baba Nanak]] in [[Gurdaspur district]] of [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] [[States and territories of India|State]], India. It is located {{convert|19|km}} from sub district headquarter and {{convert|40|km}} from district headquarter. The village is [[Administration (government)|administrated]] by [[Sarpanch]] an elected representative of the village.\n\n== Demography ==\n{{as of|2011}}, The village has a total number of 266 houses and the population of 1411 of which 751 are males while 660 are females.<ref name=census>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/DCHB_Village_Release_0300.xlsx|title=DCHB Village Release|work=[[Census of India, 2011]]}}</ref>  According to the report [[published]] by [[Census India]] in 2011, out of the total population of the village 63 people are from [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Schedule Caste]] and the village does not have any [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Schedule Tribe]] population so far.<ref name=census /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=103437|title=Child Sex Ratio in India (2001-2011)|work=pib.nic.in}}</ref><ref name=census />\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of villages in India]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.punjabtourism.gov.in/ Tourism of Punjab]\n* [http://punjabcensus.gov.in/ Census of Punjab]\n\n{{Gurdaspur district}}\n\n{{coord|31|57|N|75|02|E|display=title|region:IN_type:city_source:GNS-enwik