{"title_page": "Mike Nock", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For individuals; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Mike Nock\n| image                 = \n| alt             = \n| caption            = \n| image_size            = \n| background          = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name          = \n| alias               = \n| birth_date                = {{Birth date and age|1940|09|27|df=y}} \n|birth_place = [[Christchurch]], New Zealand\n| death_date                = \n| origin              = \n| instrument          = Piano, keyboards\n| genre               = [[Jazz]]\n| occupation          = Musician, composer, arranger\n| years_active        = \n| label               = \n| associated_acts     = \n| website                 = [http://www.mikenock.com/ mikenock.com]\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=October 2011}}\n'''Michael Anthony Nock''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|ONZM|size=85%}} (born 27 September 1940) is a New Zealand jazz pianist, currently based in Australia.\n\n==Biography==\nNock began studying piano at 11.  He attended [[Nelson College]] for one term in 1955.<ref name=\"NCOB register\">''Nelson College Old Boys' Register, 1856\u20132006'', 6th edition</ref>  By the age of 18, he was performing in Australia. He headed a trio that toured England in 1961 and then attended [[Berklee College of Music]]. He was a member of [[Yusef Lateef]]'s group from 1963 to 1965.\n\nDuring 1968\u20131970 Nock was involved with fusion, leading the [[Fourth Way]] band. After a few years he became a studio musician in New York (1975\u20131985) and then returned to Australia.\n\nHis 1987 album ''Open Door'' with drummer [[Frank Gibson, Jr.]] was named that year's Best Jazz Album in the [[New Zealand Music Awards]].\n\nIn the [[2003 New Year Honours (New Zealand)|2003 New Year Honours]], Nock was appointed an [[Officer of the New Zealand Order of Merit]], for services to jazz.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://dpmc.govt.nz/publications/new-year-honours-list-2003 | title=New Year honours list 2003 |date=31 December 2002 | publisher=Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet | accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref>\n \nHe currently lives in [[New South Wales]] where he taught at the [[Sydney Conservatorium of Music]] until 2018<ref>{{cite web | url=http://jazz.org.au/mike-nock-jazz-life/ | title=Mike Nock, A Jazz Life| date=9 September 2018 | accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref> and performs with his trio, big band, and various one-off ensembles.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===As leader===\n* ''Almanac''  ( Improvising Artists, 1967)  with [[Bennie Maupin]] / Cecil McBee / Eddie Marshall.\n* ''Between Or Beyond'' (BASF, 1970)\n* ''Magic Mansions'' (Laurie, 1977) with [[Charlie Mariano]] / [[Al Foster]]/ Ron McLure.\n* ''In, Out and Around'' ([[Timeless Muse]], 1978) with [[Michael Brecker]] / Al Foster / George Mraz.\n* ''Climbing'' (Tomato, 1979) with Tom Harrell / [[John Abercrombie (guitarist)|John Abercrombie]] / David Friesen / Al Foster.\n* ''The Opal Heart'' (Enja, 1979) with Ed Soph / Dave Liebman / Ron McClure.\n* ''Talisman'' (Inner City, 1979) Solo\n* ''Succubus'' (Sutra, 1980) with [[Alex Foster (musician)|Alex Foster]] ( saxophone ) / Ratso Harris / Tom Rainey.\n* ''Ondas'' (ECM, 1981) with Eddie Gomez / Jon Christensen.\n* ''Strata'' (Kiwi/Pacific, 1983) Solo (soundtrack)\n* ''Open Door'' (Ode, 1987) with Frank Gibson, Jr.\n* ''Beautiful Friendship'' (Ode, 1989)  with Paul Dyne / Roger Sellers.\n* ''Dark and Curious'' (Verabra, 1990) with Tim Hopkins / Cameron Undy  / Andrew Dickeson\n* ''Touch'' (Birdland, 1993) Solo\n* ''Not We But One'' (Naxos Jazz, 1996) with  Anthony Cox / Tony Reedus.\n* ''Ozboppin'' (Naxos Jazz, 1998) with  [[Phil Slater]] /  Tim Hopkins / Cameron Undy /  David Goodman.\n* ''The Waiting Game'' (Naxos Jazz, 2000) with Marty Ehrlich.\n* \"Live\" Mike Nock's BigSmallBand ( ABC Jazz 2002 ) Andrew Robson / Roger Manins / Matt Ottignon / Simon Sweeney / Dave Panichi / David Basden / Cameron Deyell / Toby Hall / Brett Hirst.\n* ''Changing Seasons'' (DIW, 2003) with Brett Hirst / Toby Hall.\n* ''Duologue '' (Birdland, 2004) Live concert  recording  with Dave Liebman.\n* ''Meeting of the Waters'' (Jazzhead Oz, 2008) The Mike Nock Project / Steve Magnusson / Julien Wilson / Tim Wilson / James Greening / Eugene Ball / Dale Gorfinkle / Toby Hall / Brett Hirst.\n* \"Andrew Klippel Compositions 1980-1983 - the Mike Nock Trio\" ( AKP0001 ) Mike Nock / James Waples / Brett  Hirst.\n* \"An Accumulation Of Subtleties\" ( FWM 001,  2010 ) The Mike Nock  Trio - with James Waples / Ben Waples.\n* \"Hear  and Know\" ( FWM 002, 2011 )  Mike Nock Trio Plus - James Waples / Ben Waples / Karl Laskowski ten sax / Ken  Allars tpt.\n*\"Transformations\" ( CD MANU5129 ) Mike Nock with The  New Zealand String Quartet - Colin Hemmingsen/Nick Tipping/ John Rae.\n* \"Kindred\"  ( FWM 003, 2012 ) Mike Nock piano / Laurenz Pike drum kit.\n* \"Suite SIMA\" ( FWM 004, 2014 ) Mike Nock Octet\n* \"Opal Dream\" ( FWM 2015 ) Howie Smith / Mike Nock\n* \"Beginning And End Of Knowing\" (FWM 2015) Mike Nock / Laurence Pike\n* \"Two - Out\" (FWM 2015) Mike Nock / Roger Manins\n* \"This World\" (LionShare 2019) Mike Nock / Hamish Stuart / Julien Wilson / Jonathan Zwartz\n\n===As sideman===\n'''With [[Tal Farlow]]'''\n*''[[Trilogy]]'' (Inner City, 1981)\n'''With [[John Handy]]'''\n*''[[Projections (John Handy album)|Projections]]'' (Columbia, 1968)\n'''With [[John Klemmer]]'''\n*''[[Waterfalls (album)|Waterfalls]]'' (Impulse ) 1972)\n*''[[Magic and Movement]]'' (Impulse!, 1974)\n'''With [[Eric Kloss]]'''\n*''[[Now (Eric Kloss album)|Now]]'' (Muse, 1978)\n'''With [[Yusef Lateef]]'''\n*''[[Live at Pep's]]'' (Impulse!)\n*''[[1984 (Yusef Lateef album)|1984]]'' (Impulse!)\n'''With [[Dave Liebman]]''' \n*''[[The Opal Heart]]'' (44, 1979)\n'''With [[The Fourth Way (band)|The Fourth Way]]'''\n*\"The Fourth Way\" (  TOCJ-50258 - Capitol - EMI ) rec 1969. \n*\"WEREWOLF\" ( TOCJ-50264 - Harvest - EMI ) rec 1970.\n*\"The Sun and Moon Have Come Together\" - Take 5 - 35014 rec 1070 .\n'''With [[Jeremy Steig]] and [[Eddie G\u00f3mez]]'''\n*''[[Rain Forest (Jeremy Steig and Eddie G\u00f3mez album)|Rain Forest]]'' (CMP, 1980)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.audioculture.co.nz/people/mike-nock AudioCulture profile]\n*[{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p7238/biography|pure_url=yes}} All Music]\n*[https://www.myspace.com/peterboothman  A Story of Jazz in Sydney - by Peter Boothman]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nock, Mike}}\n[[Category:1940 births]]\n[[Category:ARIA Award winners]]\n[[Category:Australian jazz pianists]]\n[[Category:New Zealand emigrants to Australia]]\n[[Category:Berklee College of Music alumni]]\n[[Category:DIW Records artists]]\n[[Category:ECM Records artists]]\n[[Category:Enja Records artists]]\n[[Category:Inner City Records artists]]\n[[Category:Jazz fusion pianists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:MPS Records artists]]\n[[Category:New-age pianists]]\n[[Category:New Zealand jazz pianists]]\n[[Category:People educated at Nelson College]]\n[[Category:People from Christchurch]]\n[[Category:Post-bop pianists]]\n[[Category:Timeless Records artists]]\n[[Category:Officers of the New Zealand Order of Merit]]\n[[Category:21st-century pianists]]\n[[Category:Almanac (band) members]]\n[[Category:The Fourth Way (band) members]]\n[[Category:Improvising Artists Records artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For individuals; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Mike Nock\n| image                 = \n| alt             = \n| caption            = \n| image_size            = \n| background          = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name          = \n| alias               = \n| birth_date                = {{Birth date and age|1940|09|27|df=y}} \n|birth_place = [[Christchurch]], New Zealand\n| death_date                = \n| origin              = \n| instrument          = Piano, keyboards\n| genre               = [[Jazz]]\n| occupation          = Musician, composer, arranger\n| years_active        = \n| label               = \n| associated_acts     = \n| website                 = [http://www.mikenock.com/ mikenock.com]\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=October 2011}}\n'''Michael Anthony Nock''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|ONZM|size=85%}} (born 27 September 1940) is a New Zealand jazz pianist, currently based in Australia.\n\n==Biography==\nNock began studying piano at 11.  He attended [[Nelson College]] for one term in 1955.<ref name=\"NCOB register\">''Nelson College Old Boys' Register, 1856\u20132006'', 6th edition</ref>  By the age of 18, he was performing in Australia. He headed a trio that toured England in 1961 and then attended [[Berklee College of Music]]. He was a member of [[Yusef Lateef]]'s group from 1963 to 1965.\n\nDuring 1968\u20131970 Nock was involved with fusion, leading the [[Fourth Way]] band. After a few years he became a studio musician in New York (1975\u20131985) and then returned to Australia.\n\nHis 1987 album ''Open Door'' with drummer [[Frank Gibson, Jr.]] was named that year's Best Jazz Album in the [[New Zealand Music Awards]].\n\nIn the [[2003 New Year Honours (New Zealand)|2003 New Year Honours]], Nock was appointed an [[Officer of the New Zealand Order of Merit]], for services to jazz.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://dpmc.govt.nz/publications/new-year-honours-list-2003 | title=New Year honours list 2003 |date=31 December 2002 | publisher=Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet | accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref>\n \nHe currently lives in [[New South Wales]] where he taught at the [[Sydney Conservatorium of Music]] until 2018{{cite web | url=http://jazz.org.au/mike-nock-jazz-life/ | title=Mike Nock, A Jazz Life| date=9 September 2018 | accessdate=18 April 2020}} and performs with his trio, big band, and various one-off ensembles.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===As leader===\n* ''Almanac''  ( Improvising Artists, 1967)  with [[Bennie Maupin]] / Cecil McBee / Eddie Marshall.\n* ''Between Or Beyond'' (BASF, 1970)\n* ''Magic Mansions'' (Laurie, 1977) with [[Charlie Mariano]] / [[Al Foster]]/ Ron McLure.\n* ''In, Out and Around'' ([[Timeless Muse]], 1978) with [[Michael Brecker]] / Al Foster / George Mraz.\n* ''Climbing'' (Tomato, 1979) with Tom Harrell / [[John Abercrombie (guitarist)|John Abercrombie]] / David Friesen / Al Foster.\n* ''The Opal Heart'' (Enja, 1979) with Ed Soph / Dave Liebman / Ron McClure.\n* ''Talisman'' (Inner City, 1979) Solo\n* ''Succubus'' (Sutra, 1980) with [[Alex Foster (musician)|Alex Foster]] ( saxophone ) / Ratso Harris / Tom Rainey.\n* ''Ondas'' (ECM, 1981) with Eddie Gomez / Jon Christensen.\n* ''Strata'' (Kiwi/Pacific, 1983) Solo (soundtrack)\n* ''Open Door'' (Ode, 1987) with Frank Gibson, Jr.\n* ''Beautiful Friendship'' (Ode, 1989)  with Paul Dyne / Roger Sellers.\n* ''Dark and Curious'' (Verabra, 1990) with Tim Hopkins / Cameron Undy  / Andrew Dickeson\n* ''Touch'' (Birdland, 1993) Solo\n* ''Not We But One'' (Naxos Jazz, 1996) with  Anthony Cox / Tony Reedus.\n* ''Ozboppin'' (Naxos Jazz, 1998) with  [[Phil Slater]] /  Tim Hopkins / Cameron Undy /  David Goodman.\n* ''The Waiting Game'' (Naxos Jazz, 2000) with Marty Ehrlich.\n* \"Live\" Mike Nock's BigSmallBand ( ABC Jazz 2002 ) Andrew Robson / Roger Manins / Matt Ottignon / Simon Sweeney / Dave Panichi / David Basden / Cameron Deyell / Toby Hall / Brett Hirst.\n* ''Changing Seasons'' (DIW, 2003) with Brett Hirst / Toby Hall.\n* ''Duologue '' (Birdland, 2004) Live concert  recording  with Dave Liebman.\n* ''Meeting of the Waters'' (Jazzhead Oz, 2008) The Mike Nock Project / Steve Magnusson / Julien Wilson / Tim Wilson / James Greening / Eugene Ball / Dale Gorfinkle / Toby Hall / Brett Hirst.\n* \"Andrew Klippel Compositions 1980-1983 - the Mike Nock Trio\" ( AKP0001 ) Mike Nock / James Waples / Brett  Hirst.\n* \"An Accumulation Of Subtleties\" ( FWM 001,  2010 ) The Mike Nock  Trio - with James Waples / Ben Waples.\n* \"Hear  and Know\" ( FWM 002, 2011 )  Mike Nock Trio Plus - James Waples / Ben Waples / Karl Laskowski ten sax / Ken  Allars tpt.\n*\"Transformations\" ( CD MANU5129 ) Mike Nock with The  New Zealand String Quartet - Colin Hemmingsen/Nick Tipping/ John Rae.\n* \"Kindred\"  ( FWM 003, 2012 ) Mike Nock piano / Laurenz Pike drum kit.\n* \"Suite SIMA\" ( FWM 004, 2014 ) Mike Nock Octet\n* \"Opal Dream\" ( FWM 2015 ) Howie Smith / Mike Nock\n* \"Beginning And End Of Knowing\" (FWM 2015) Mike Nock / Laurence Pike\n* \"Two - Out\" (FWM 2015) Mike Nock / Roger Manins\n* \"This World\" (LionShare 2019) Mike Nock / Hamish Stuart / Julien Wilson / Jonathan Zwartz\n\n===As sideman===\n'''With [[Tal Farlow]]'''\n*''[[Trilogy]]'' (Inner City, 1981)\n'''With [[John Handy]]'''\n*''[[Projections (John Handy album)|Projections]]'' (Columbia, 1968)\n'''With [[John Klemmer]]'''\n*''[[Waterfalls (album)|Waterfalls]]'' (Impulse ) 1972)\n*''[[Magic and Movement]]'' (Impulse!, 1974)\n'''With [[Eric Kloss]]'''\n*''[[Now (Eric Kloss album)|Now]]'' (Muse, 1978)\n'''With [[Yusef Lateef]]'''\n*''[[Live at Pep's]]'' (Impulse!)\n*''[[1984 (Yusef Lateef album)|1984]]'' (Impulse!)\n'''With [[Dave Liebman]]''' \n*''[[The Opal Heart]]'' (44, 1979)\n'''With [[The Fourth Way (band)|The Fourth Way]]'''\n*\"The Fourth Way\" (  TOCJ-50258 - Capitol - EMI ) rec 1969. \n*\"WEREWOLF\" ( TOCJ-50264 - Harvest - EMI ) rec 1970.\n*\"The Sun and Moon Have Come Together\" - Take 5 - 35014 rec 1070 .\n'''With [[Jeremy Steig]] and [[Eddie G\u00f3mez]]'''\n*''[[Rain Forest (Jeremy Steig and Eddie G\u00f3mez album)|Rain Forest]]'' (CMP, 1980)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.audioculture.co.nz/people/mike-nock AudioCulture profile]\n*[{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p7238/biography|pure_url=yes}} All Music]\n*[https://www.myspace.com/peterboothman  A Story of Jazz in Sydney - by Peter Boothman]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nock, Mike}}\n[[Category:1940 births]]\n[[Category:ARIA Award winners]]\n[[Category:Australian jazz pianists]]\n[[Category:New Zealand emigrants to Australia]]\n[[Category:Berklee College of Music alumni]]\n[[Category:DIW Records artists]]\n[[Category:ECM Records artists]]\n[[Category:Enja Records artists]]\n[[Category:Inner City Records artists]]\n[[Category:Jazz fusion pianists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:MPS Records artists]]\n[[Category:New-age pianists]]\n[[Category:New Zealand jazz pianists]]\n[[Category:People educated at Nelson College]]\n[[Category:People from Christchurch]]\n[[Category:Post-bop pianists]]\n[[Category:Timeless Records artists]]\n[[Category:Officers of the New Zealand Order of Merit]]\n[[Category:21st-century pianists]]\n[[Category:Almanac (band) members]]\n[[Category:The Fourth Way (band) members]]\n[[Category:Improvising Artists Records artists]]\n", "name_user": "Andrewlorien", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBiography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Nock"}
